{#- docs/GENERATIONS.md — full projection of .specify/generations.ttl.
    G0/G1 facts and the 15-condition doctrine table are all gen: individuals;
    nothing in this template is authored prose beyond fixed headings. -#}
{%- set g0 = sparql(query='PREFIX gen: <http://ggen.org/generations#> SELECT ?commit ?commitSubject ?workspaceVersion ?toolchain ?binaryStanding WHERE { gen:G0 a gen:Generation ; gen:commit ?commit ; gen:commitSubject ?commitSubject ; gen:workspaceVersion ?workspaceVersion ; gen:toolchain ?toolchain ; gen:binaryStanding ?binaryStanding . }') | first -%}
{%- set g1 = sparql(query='PREFIX gen: <http://ggen.org/generations#> SELECT ?rootManifestRuleCountBefore ?rootManifestRuleCountAfter ?bookOutputFileCountBefore ?bookChapterLinksBefore ?bookChapterLinksAfter ?claudeCodePackDeclaredOutputs ?claudeCodePackOutputsPresentOnDisk ?selfHostedEvidenceLoopScript ?selfHostedEvidenceLoopExitsZeroAlways WHERE { gen:G1 a gen:Generation ; gen:rootManifestRuleCountBefore ?rootManifestRuleCountBefore ; gen:rootManifestRuleCountAfter ?rootManifestRuleCountAfter ; gen:bookOutputFileCountBefore ?bookOutputFileCountBefore ; gen:bookChapterLinksBefore ?bookChapterLinksBefore ; gen:bookChapterLinksAfter ?bookChapterLinksAfter ; gen:claudeCodePackDeclaredOutputs ?claudeCodePackDeclaredOutputs ; gen:claudeCodePackOutputsPresentOnDisk ?claudeCodePackOutputsPresentOnDisk ; gen:selfHostedEvidenceLoopScript ?selfHostedEvidenceLoopScript ; gen:selfHostedEvidenceLoopExitsZeroAlways ?selfHostedEvidenceLoopExitsZeroAlways . }') | first -%}
{%- set dod = sparql(query='PREFIX gen: <http://ggen.org/generations#> SELECT ?order ?text ?status ?evidence WHERE { ?c a gen:DoDCondition ; gen:order ?order ; gen:text ?text ; gen:status ?status ; gen:evidence ?evidence . } ORDER BY ?order') -%}
{%- set met_count = dod | filter(attribute="status", value="MET") | length -%}
# Generation Ledger

GENERATED by `ggen sync` from `.specify/generations.ttl` — edit the ontology, not this file.

This ledger names two generations: **G0**, the manufacturing state this round started
from, and **G1**, what this round manufactures. The split exists so that no single round
certifies its own output — G1 records what it built; a later, separately-receipted round
must inspect it before any row below may move from NOT MET to MET on that round's own say-so.

## G0 — starting state

| Fact | Value |
|---|---|
| Commit | `{{ g0.commit }}` |
| Commit subject | {{ g0.commitSubject }} |
| Workspace version (`Cargo.toml` `[workspace.package]`) | {{ g0.workspaceVersion }} |
| Toolchain (`rust-toolchain.toml`) | {{ g0.toolchain }} |
| Binary standing | `{{ g0.binaryStanding }}` |

## G1 — what this round manufactures

| Fact | Value |
|---|---|
| Root `ggen.toml` `[[generation.rules]]` count (before → after) | {{ g1.rootManifestRuleCountBefore }} → {{ g1.rootManifestRuleCountAfter }} |
| `book/src/` output file count (before this round's chapter addition) | {{ g1.bookOutputFileCountBefore }} |
| `book/scripts/check_book.py` chapter-links count, before | {{ g1.bookChapterLinksBefore }} |
| `book/scripts/check_book.py` chapter-links count, after | {{ g1.bookChapterLinksAfter }} |
| `claude-code-pack` declared `.claude/` outputs | {{ g1.claudeCodePackDeclaredOutputs }} |
| ...of which present on disk today | {{ g1.claudeCodePackOutputsPresentOnDisk }} |
| Self-hosted evidence-loop script | `{{ g1.selfHostedEvidenceLoopScript }}` |
| ...always exits 0 (records reality; gates judge it separately) | {{ g1.selfHostedEvidenceLoopExitsZeroAlways }} |

